# MyTypist — Cursor Rules (main app)

READ `../ai-rules/MASTER.md` (or `ai-rules/MASTER.md` from repo root) BEFORE WRITING ANY UI CODE.

## Project
- Stack: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite, raw CSS with CSS variables, Zustand, Motion, Swiper
- Code here in: `src/`
- Accent: `#6C47FF` | Currency: ₦ only | Mobile-first CSS

## Hard Banned
- Soft gradients, glassmorphism, oversized radii (>10px cards, >8px buttons), pill overload
- 3-column equal feature cards, `Inter` as default font
- Em-dashes (`—`), pure `#000`/`#fff`
- `window.addEventListener('scroll', ...)` — use `useScroll()` from motion/react
- Fake product UIs from `<div>` rectangles, metric-card grids as dashboard default

## What Good Looks Like — Linear, Raycast, Stripe, GitHub
- Sidebars: 240-260px, solid bg, 1px border-right
- Buttons: 8-10px radius, solid fill only
- Cards: 8-12px radius, 1px border, shadow ≤ 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08)
- Transitions: 100-200ms ease

## Installed
- `motion` → `import { motion } from "motion/react"`
- `swiper` → `import { Swiper, SwiperSlide } from 'swiper/react'`
- `lucide-react` — icons (already installed)

## Component Sources
1. `npx shadcn@latest add [component]`
2. `npx shadcn@latest add [21st.dev URL]`
3. `npx shadcn@latest add https://efferd.com/r/[block-name].json`

## 3D / Spline — STOP
Do not build in Three.js. See `ai-rules/spline-handoff.md`. Give user a Spline AI prompt. Wait.

